<L>Saemina &amp; incultum maereo jacta &s;olum.</L>
<L>Sed &s;ero &s;apimus, nimium &s;ors Lector amica</L>
<L>Impediit &s;tudiis invigilare meis.</L>
<L>Dum fortuna favet mens ebria &s;urgit in altum,</L>
<L>Optima &s;ors hominum pe&s;&s;ima corda facit,</L>
<L>Saepe donum e&s;t carui&s;&s;e bonis, &amp; ferre mole&s;ta</L>
<L>Nam pro&s;unt multis tri&s;tia, laeta nocent,</L>
<L><PB REF="26">A&s;t humiles animi &s;unt rebus &s;aepe &s;ub arctis</L>
<L>Di&s;cinctos mores fata &s;ini&s;tra fugant.</L>
