<L>Vos, animae illu&s;tres, vano valedicite mundo,</L>
<L>Vos decet aethereis nunc inhiare bonis.</L>
<L>Invi&s;is tandem mentes &s;ubducite terris</L>
<L>Hic ubi &s;pes &s;emper lubrica, vita brevis.</L>
<L>Jam coelum coeli a&s;picitis, jam proxima vita</L>
<L>In vi&s;u e&s;t, retro vertere vela nefas.</L>
<L>Carpite iter coeli, quibus e&s;t coele&s;tis origo,</L>
<L>Terra nihil pulchri, quod videatis, habet.</L>
</DIV2>
<DIV2>
<PB REF="39">
<Q>De Conver&s;ione Sancti Pauli.</Q>
<L>Terrorum plenus Solym&ucirc;m frendebat in oris</L>
<L>Saulus, dum ca&s;&s;um lumine pectus erat:</L>
<L>Annuit ad mortem Stephani, &s;piratque furorem</L>
<L>In cunctos etiam qui coluere Deum.</L>
<L>Ad &s;acra dum ridet Chri&s;ti my&s;teria Saulus,</L>
<L>De coelo &s;ubitum &s;entit ade&s;&s;e Deum:</L>
<L>Apparuit Chri&s;tus Saulo, vox faucibus hae&s;it,</L>
<L>Et jacuit toto corpore fu&s;us humi.</L>
<L>Dum manet immotus, morum tamen ore fatetur,</L>
<L>Vivit, &amp; e&s;t virae ne&s;cius ip&s;e &s;uae.</L>
<L>Omnipotens Verbi Divini fulmen ad aures</L>
<L>Demi&s;&s;um Sauli fulmine corda quatit:</L>
<L>Obvenit &amp; ip&s;i divini &s;tamma furoris,</L>
<L>Flamma vel extinctas docta ciere faces:</L>
<L>Et Deus ip&s;e &s;uo di&s;ponens omnia nutu,</L>
<L>Saulum ex obliqua mandat abire via.</L>
<L>Sic Deus hoc lap&s;u Sauli ve&s;tigia flectit,</L>
<L>Ire pedes coepit, qui prius ibat eques.</L>
<L>Quod magis admiror, velocius ultra &s;ubivit,</L>
<L>Quam cum p$ecipiti curreret actus equo.</L>
<L>Haec &s;trages optanda fuit, &s;uccumbere Chri&s;to,</L>
<L>Haec fit ovis &s;ubit&ograve;, qui ferus ante lupus.</L>
<L>Quam gravis hic lap&s;us! quam pul&s;at pectora Chri&s;tus</L>
<L>Quam &s;uo praecipiti fulmine corda quatit!</L>
<L>Quae rerum foeces! nunc, quem de&s;pexit, adorat;</L>
<L>Nunc ante ignotum praedicat ore Deum.</L>
<L>Qui lupus ore gregem Chri&s;ti ab&s;orbere parabat,</L>
<L>Quam cito, mutato vellere, factus ovis.</L>
<L>Saulus erat, modo Paulus abit; qui pe&s;&s;imus ante</L>
<L>Ho&s;tis erat Chri&s;ti, verus amicus ade&s;t.</L>
<L>Illico mota calent flammis &s;ua pectora &s;acris,</L>
<L>Saulus &amp; en lap&s;u cel&s;ior ip&s;e &s;uo.</L>
<L><PB REF="40">Lumine prae nimio fit Saulus luminis expers,</L>
<L>Protinus ut melius cerneret ille Deum.</L>
<L>Attrahit aethereo nigram de lumine noctem,</L>
<L>Stant oculis tenebrae, mente &s;erena dies.</L>
<L>Illa &s;uos foelix caligo texit ocellos,</L>
<L>Ut lucem coecis gentibus ille daret:</L>
<L>Et quamvis coeli privatus lumine, lucem,</L>
<L>Qua &s;e, quaque Deum con&s;picit, intus habet.</L>
<L>Foelici lap&s;u &s;ic vi&s;um perdidit, &amp; cum</L>
<L>Perdidit ille oculos, repperit ille novos.</L>
<L>Hinc venit ut Paulus toti innote&s;cere mundo</L>
<L>Coepit, &amp; ex illo clarior e&s;&s;e die.</L>
<L>Ignea mens Pauli &s;plendet, vox fulminis in&s;tar,</L>
<L>Doctaque coele&s;tis pectora flammat amor.</L>
<L>Undique vicinas volitabat fama per urbes;</L>
<L>Tam &s;ubito Domini venit ab ore &s;alus.</L>
<L>Quanta tuum in Paulum e&s;t clementia, Rector Olympi,</L>
<L>Qui moribund&acirc; nova lumina luce beas!</L>
<L>Qui lupus ante rapax ve&s;titur vellere molli,</L>
<L>Seductor quondam qui modo ductor ade&s;t</L>
<L>Jam tuba plena Dei, &s;ed quondam plena furore,</L>
<L>Nunc &amp; inexhau&s;ti vas &s;ine labe boni.</L>
<L>Utque aliis e&s;&s;et lumen, &s;ua lumina perdit,</L>
<L>Coecus cernit, erat coecus &amp; ip&s;e videns:</L>
<L>Mox late rutilans infundit lumina mundo,</L>
<L>Coecorum e&s;t medicus, qui modo coecus erat.</L>
</DIV2>
<DIV2>
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q><P>De Nuptiis in Cana Galileae, ubi aqua in vi|num vertitur.</P>
<BIBL><HI>Joann. 2.</HI></BIBL></Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<L>Solennes Epulas, &amp; connubialia Fe&s;ta</L>
<L>Dum Galilaea parat, Chri&s;tus ade&s;&s;e petit;</L>
<L>Ac invitatis facilis conviva recumbit;</L>
<L>Sic vacat exiguis rebus ade&s;&s;e Jovi.</L>
<L><PB REF="41">Ut ponunt men&s;ae &s;ua &s;ercula grata &s;ecundae,</L>
<L>Mater ait Chri&s;to; deficit ecce merum.</L>
<L>Mox mandat Chri&s;tus (cui tanta potentia verbo?)</L>
<L>Et vitem fa&s;&s;a e&s;t hanc pia lympha &s;uam.</L>
<L>Dulcius vel citius nequit de palmite ferre</L>
<L>Quam faecunda &s;cyphis vox tuis una dedit.</L>
<L>In vinum liquidae vertuntur fluminis undae,</L>
<L>Va&s;aque divino plena liquore rubent;</L>
<L>Nutu divino proprium mutantque colorem:</L>
<L>Lympha pudica Deum vidit, &amp; erubuit.</L>
<L>Incipit in florem dulcis tran&s;ire Falerni,</L>
<L>Ac invitatis gaudia mira dedit.</L>
<L>Ob&s;tupuit &s;pon&s;us, famulorum &amp; concita turb</L>
<L>Non expectantes talia dona meri.</L>
<L>Sic fontem viventis aquae quem &s;aepe vocarunt,</L>
<L>Te fontem vini, Chri&s;te, vocare volo.</L>
<L>Elicuit Mo&s;es duplici cum verbere lymphas;</L>
<L>Elicit hic verbo vina Falerna &s;uo.</L>
<L>Mutat aquas vino: nec Chri&s;ti munera &s;perne,</L>
<L>Sed bibe; delicias fons habet i&s;te &s;uas.</L>
<L>Pergite coele&s;tem &s;ic evacuare liquorem,</L>
<L>Ebrius hinc ni&s;i &s;is, &s;obrius e&s;&s;e nequis.</L>
</DIV2>
<DIV2>
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q><P>Nie$dumus veniens per noctem ad Chri&s;tum.</P>
<BIBL><HI>Joann. 2.</HI></BIBL></Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<L>Quid tenchras luci prefers, noctemque diei?</L>
<L>Hic f$cit ex umbris lumina, nocte diem.</L>
<L>Non tenebris divinus amor fu&s;catur ab i&s;tis,</L>
<L>Sed noctem &egrave; media nocte repellit amor.</L>
<L>Invenis in tenebris Chri&s;tum, Nicodeme; tenebras</L>
<L>Luce &s;ui vultus di&s;&s;ipat ille tuas.</L>
<L>Ergo tuas has per tenebras di&s;pelle tenebras,</L>
<L>Arque ex hac, noctem di&s;cute, nocte, tuam</L>
</DIV2>
<DIV2>
<PB REF="42">
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q><P>De Filio prodigo.</P>
<BIBL><HI>Luc. 11.</HI></BIBL></Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<L>Prodigus en haeres effrons depo&s;cere gazas,</L>
<L>Vi&s;us &amp; &agrave; patria perditus ire domo.</L>
<L>Filius hic demens, qui patri cedere ne&s;cit,</L>
<L>Qui facienda fugit, qui fugienda facit.</L>
<L>Mens vaga di&s;currit, quoque menti con&s;onat aetas,</L>
<L>Mentis &amp; aetatis turbine froena fugit.</L>
<L>Solliciti patris ju&s;&s;is parere recu&s;ans,</L>
<L>Effatus tales fudit ab ore &s;onos:</L>
<L>Pignora da, genitor, per quae tua vera propago</L>
<L>Credar, quae petiit pignora datque pater.</L>
<L>Ut data &s;unt, juvenis peregrinas tendit in oras</L>
<L>Et procul &agrave; patriis di&s;&s;ita regna focis.</L>
<L>Ibat ovans, alacri juvenum &s;tipante caterva,</L>
<L>Alterius longas orbis ad u&s;que plagas.</L>
<L>Jamque in &s;u&s;tra ruit, vacuas perpotus ad aures,</L>
<L>Lux Baccho, Veneri &s;ervit amica quies.</L>
<L>Pergraecando ro&s;as inter molle&s;que Choreas</L>
<L>Laena fuit nummis infidio&s;a &s;uis.</L>
<L>Quid facis ah demens? quae te male&s;uada voluptas</L>
<L>Du$it in obliquam ventre jubente viam?</L>
<L>Qui mandata patris, vel dogmata &s;ancta &s;ophorum</L>
<L>Negligit, aut &s;pernit; quam mi&s;er ille perit.</L>
<L>Cui corpus, cui colla regit violenta cupido</L>
<L>Colla licet jactat libera, &s;ervus erit.</L>
<L>Di&s;&s;ipat hic patris cen&s;us, mox urget ege&s;tas</L>
<L>Et mendicato cogitur ip&s;e ciho.</L>
<L>Hic canum hoc rutilis praefert male &s;edibus, i&s;tas</L>
<L>Hic male &s;purcitias diligit ante Deum.</L>
<L>Ah! pudet amplecti qua&s;i dulcia cinnama coenum,</L>
<L>Et &s;iliquis animum pa&s;cere, corda luto.</L>
<L>D$liciis jam finis erat, vili&s;&s;ima vent$em</L>
<L>Pabula jam cogit pa&s;cere dira fames.</L>
<L><PB REF="43">Mox &s;timulante &s;ame duras quatit illice glandes,</L>
<L>Et &s;uis indignos quaeritat e&s;&s;e cibos.</L>
<L>Fercula &s;unt &s;ordes cinerum, farri&s;que canini</L>
<L>Relliquiae; clamat voce manuque, date;</L>
<L>Et manus &egrave;que manu tenus cecid&ecirc;re malignis</L>
<L>De dapibus micae, &s;i modo mica dapes.</L>
<L>Jam &s;tomachum &s;ubit aegra fames, praecordia vexat,</L>
<L>Occulto latrant ilia rauca &s;ono.</L>
<L>Longa &s;ames genuum juncturas laxat, &amp; extant</L>
<L>O&s;&s;a per exanguem dinumeranda cutem.</L>
<L>Ventris erat pro ventre locus&punc; pendere putares</L>
<L>Pectus, &amp; in vultu mortis imago fuit.</L>
<L>Quae modo purpureis proeful&s;it gloria cunis,</L>
<L>Nunc latet in panno paupere, &s;quallor habet.</L>
<L>Inde memor patriae tandem, men&s;aeque paternae,</L>
<L>Ingemit, &amp; &s;ecum talia volvit iners.</L>
<L>Qu&ograve; male &s;ane ruis&punc; tenerorum oblite parentum,</L>
<L>O oblite tui, qu&ograve; male &s;ane ruis?</L>
<L>Tandem po&s;t dubios &s;edet haec &s;ententia fluctus,</L>
<L>Se patris in medium praecipitare &s;inum.</L>
<L>Protinus a&s;&s;urgit charum repetendo parentem,</L>
<L>Atque has jejuno protulit ore preces.</L>
<L>Oh pater! exundant gemini qua&s;i flumina rivi,</L>
<L>Oh pater! elinguis vinxit ad ora &s;tupor.</L>
<L>F$ccavi pater, ab quo me ve&s;ania quo me</L>
<L>Impulit heu coeco coeca juventa pede;</L>
<L>Da veniam ca$pae, pater, o pater optime, clama$.</L>
<L>Te rogo per patrii quidquid amoris habes.</L>
<L>In$lama&punc; ocjurga, coelique, tuique, meique</L>
<L>Immemorem; ingratum degenerem&abque; voca.</L>
<L>Vincula &s;i merui, &s;i erga&s;tula, laetus obibo,</L>
<L>Si me mancipium vis fore laetus ero.</L>
<L>Hoc unum obte&s;tor, fieri, pater optime, nato</L>
<L>Ut recress pauco mortua membra cibo;</L>
<L>Tantum ut edam micas, &amp; fru&s;tula panis ade&s;i</L>
<L>Et quae non merui dentibus o&s;&s;a teram.</L>
<L><PB REF="44">Nil mihi cum vitulo, &s;tola candida, nil mihi tecum</L>
<L>Non e&s;t conveniens hic cibus, ille color.</L>
<L>Inde pater motus nati prece, brachia tendit</L>
<L>Mox &amp; in amplexus &s;e jubet ire &s;uos.</L>
<L>Prodigus ille domum rediit Germanus, &amp; ecce</L>
<L>Tota domus plau&s;u laetitiaque &s;trepit.</L>
<L>Ornabat nati lumbos Holo&s;erica ve&s;tis,</L>
<L>Tinctaque purpureo murice ve&s;tis erat.</L>
<L>Jamque &s;aginatus genero&s;o &s;anguine cultrum</L>
<L>Imbuit, &amp; vitulus vi&s;us amare necem e&s;t.</L>
<L>Dicat adhinc proles patrium &s;ervare favorem,</L>
<L>Et di&s;cat quanto flagrat amore pater.</L>
<L>Ut piget hunc &s;celeris, genitor &s;celus omne remittit,</L>
<L>Et &s;ua pacifico brachia more parat;</L>
<L>Poenitet illicitae quem Vitae, &amp; con&s;cius error</L>
<L>Quem praemit, in Coelis gloria major erit.</L>
<L>Nec cupit ut pereant peccati pondere pre&s;&s;i,</L>
<L>Sed magis ut vivant &amp; relevetur onus.</L>
<L>Sed di&s;cat proles dum Patris &s;pernit habenas,</L>
<L>Quas meruit poenas filius, ip&s;e luit.</L>
<L>Prodigus hic porcos glande&s;que pero&s;us, amantem</L>
<L>Longinqu&acirc; repetit de regione Patrem.</L>
<L>Vos regio longinqua tenet, vos pa&s;cere porcos,</L>
<L>Vos &s;iliquis pa&s;tos Patre carere juvat:</L>
<L>O peregrinantes mi&s;eri qui tenditis illuc,</L>
<L>Spretus ubi aeterno vos cremet igne Pater.</L>
<L>Vos tandem remeate ad fulcrum dulce parentis,</L>
<L>Exemplo doctus quilibet e&s;to &s;uo.</L>
</DIV2>
<DIV2>
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q><BIBL><HI>Joann. 10.</HI></BIBL>
<P>Bonus Pa&s;tor dabit animam pro o|vibus.</P></Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<L>Pa&s;toris fict&agrave; &s;ub imagine ce&s;&s;it Olympo,</L>
<L>Admaeti teneras pa&s;cere Phoebus Oves.</L>
<L><PB REF="45">Sol no&s;ter petiit Cereris &s;ub imagine terras,</L>
<L>E&s;&s;e ut idem ovibus Pa&s;tor &amp; E&s;ca &s;uis.</L>
<L>Blandus &amp; opilio mi&s;erum &amp; pa&s;cit Ie&s;us,</L>
<L>Per &s;alebras gre&s;&s;us dirigit ille tuos,</L>
<L>Cum procul a Pa&s;tore Deo tu devius i&s;ti,</L>
<L>Protinus imbellem te revocarit ovem.</L>
<L>Te tenet ac inter mor&s;us rict&uacute;&s;que ferarum,</L>
<L>Excubias &s;acro pro grege &s;emper agit.</L>
<L>Caetera pa&s;torum gens gaudet &s;orte benign&acirc;,</L>
<L>I&s;te lupis pavido pro grege bella gerit.</L>
<L>Qu&agrave;m bonus e&s;t Pa&s;tor, qui non detrectat acerbam</L>
<L>Pro grege Servando fortis adire necem!</L>
<L>Quim bonus e&s;t Pa&s;tor qui &s;acrificabitur agnis!</L>
<L>Sic erit &ocirc; &s;ic non Pa&s;tor ut Agnus erit.</L>
<L>Agnus erit &s;ine labe Crucis mactandus ad aras,</L>
<L>Peccatis hominum Victima grata cadet.</L>
<L>Victima grata cadet nec &s;acrificabitur ulla,</L>
<L>Ho&s;tia digna Deo ni Deus ip&s;e cadat.</L>
<L>Quam praecor indomitam cruor hic non leniat iram</L>
<L>Ira e$ hoc gu&s;tans Sanguine, mitis erit.</L>
</DIV2>
<DIV2>
<EPIGRAPH>
<Q><BIBL><HI>Apoc. 12.</HI></BIBL>
<P>Pugna Draconis cum S. Michaele.</P></Q>
</EPIGRAPH>
<L>Angelici caetus Princeps juhet arma parari</L>
<L>Lucifer, &amp; &s;ocios raptar in arma &s;uos.</L>
<L>Scilicet affectans &s;olium &s;ublime Tonantis,</L>
<L>En quatit in &s;ummum tela cruenta Deum.</L>
<L>Proh pudor! impatiens Maje&s;tati&s;&abque; &s;ecundae</L>
<L>Po&s;tulat in&s;ultans &s;ceptra &s;uprema poli;</L>
<L>Author$m&abque; &s;uum &s;pernit, Domino&abque; rebelles</L>
<L>Aetheris indigenas &s;ub &s;ua &s;igna trahit.</L>
<L>O quantes in bella duces! quae protulit arma</L>
<L>Perfidus, &amp; quant&acirc; praelia dira tuba!</L>
<L>Quantus in aethereis tollit &s;e Lucifer armis!</L>
<L>At&abque; ip&s;o graditur vix Michaele minor!</L>
<L><PB REF="46">Quantis &amp; quam fune&s;tis concurritur iris!</L>
<L>Dum ferus hic &s;tellas protegit, ille rapit!</L>
<L>Dum vul&s;os montes ceu tela reciproca torquent,</L>
<L>Et non mortali de&s;uper igne pluunt.</L>
<L>Vibrantur flammae, commotu tonitrua rauco</L>
<L>Admi&s;tis flammis in&s;onu&ecirc;re polo,</L>
<L>Ac &s;imul in coelis Me&s;&s;iae in&s;ignia fulgent</L>
<L>Cum Cruce Vexilla, praeda cruenta, Dei.</L>
<L>Attamen aethereis non cedet Lucifer armis</L>
<L>Et metuit pugnae non &s;upere&s;&s;e &s;uae.</L>
<L>O indigne poli fallax augere triumphos!</L>
<L>Audes tam certas &s;ollicitare manus?</L>
<L>Falleris heu mult&ugrave;m, vanos raptaris in au&s;us</L>
<L>In &s;uperos tragic&acirc; praelia flare tuba.</L>
<L>Tu coelum furiis agitas, agitatus ii&s;dem</L>
<L>Ter mi&s;er aetherei vindicis igne cades!</L>
<L>Confe&s;tim mi&s;&s;us cum fulminis igne, videbis</L>
<L>Ip&s;e tuas tenebras, lux ubi nulla nitet.</L>
<L>In&s;anum e&s;t certare Deo cui milirat aether,</L>
<L>Cum propriis armis illic&ograve; vinctus eris.</L>
<L>Quippe novum acquirit Michael certamine robur,</L>
<L>Quo magis &amp; premitur, tollitur ille magis.</L>
<L>Sub pedibu&s;&abque; &s;uis jacet admirabile mon&s;trum,</L>
<L>Et Sceptrum victi grande Draconis habet.</L>
<L>Sic cadit attonitis mens omnis, &amp; impetus omnis,</L>
<L>Et ca&s;&s;is dextris irrita tela cadunt.</L>
<L>Ad poenas fugiunt, &amp; ceu foret Orcus a&s;ylum,</L>
<L>Infernis certant condere &s;e tenebris.</L>
<L>Dum Michael Victor &s;poliis &amp; henoribus auctus</L>
<L>Luciferi, &s;tellis, Lauro imitante, nitet.</L>
